    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling core, anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (77.06) and **Jackson Merrill** (74.85), our top two projected producers. **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a strong matchup against Alcantara, where a combination of wind favoring hitters and a high xwOBA projection makes him our primary anchor. **Jackson Merrill** is similarly positioned for an elite output, leveraging a 10% boost from his leadoff spot and a 13% efficiency gain against Taillon. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (74.84) also grades out as a must-start, as his significant BvP historical edge against Bello helps offset the dynamic platoon impact, keeping him firmly in the 70+ \"Strong\" tier.\n\nOur strategy regarding stolen bases remains front and center, with **Josh Lowe** (71.68) serving as the day\u2019s \"hidden gem.\" While he faces Fedde, his score is bolstered by a 19% SP skill advantage and a critical 2% efficiency bump for the matchup against a slower-delivering pitcher, which statistically increases his success rate for a stolen base attempt. The most difficult bench decision was bypassing **Marcell Ozuna** (57.35). While his base projection is solid, the optimizer prioritized the positional flexibility and higher categorical utility of **Jacob Wilson** and **Miguel Vargas**, both of whom maintain better overall efficiency ratings despite **Marcell Ozuna**\u2019s respectable metrics against Pallante.\n\nThe lineup carries moderate risk at the catcher position, where **Drake Baldwin** faces an uphill battle against the elite arm of Skubal (2.71 xERA). Despite a respectable score, his production is heavily stifled by the SP\u2019s dominant skill level, making him a candidate for volatility. Additionally, we must monitor the status of **Gunnar Henderson**, who remains on the bench due to a confirmed rainout. We are avoiding the temptation to force him into a lineup spot, ensuring we preserve our daily game caps for the high-efficiency matchups elsewhere. With **Liam Hicks** and **Nasim Nunez** providing serviceable returns in the bottom half of the order, we are well-positioned to chase volume and SB efficiency tonight.",
